                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.01/32: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-13T15:00:00-03:00"
                            >October 13, 1933—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>91. Minister for Foreign Affairs would value any information as to our progress
                    toward recognition of Cuban government. Says he <pb facs="0572" n="484"
                        xml:id="pg_484"/> is anxious to follow our lead in this matter of primary
                    interest to us but is now at a disadvantage in standing off pressure for
                    recognition through lack of up-to-date information. Suggest Department keep me
                    advised of developments from time to time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
